and Lord of the Isles) forfeited his lands, his power, and his title as Lord of the Isles in 1493 to King James IV of Scotland. By then, a branch of the family had settled in the Antrim Glens in Ireland and members moved between the southern Hebrides and Ireland throughout the 16th century."]}]},{"name":"Allan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alan  , used mainly in Scotland and North America."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Allan MacDonald 2nd of Clanranald and Moidart was born in 1350, in Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Ranald Reginald Macdonald 1st Of Clanranald And Glengarry, was 5 and his mother, Lady Fiona Stewart of Atholl, was 3. He had at least 1 daughter with Mary Stewart. He died in 1429, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1350–1429":"1350–1429","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1375–1442":"1375–1442","1345–1386":"1345–1386","1347–1390":"1347–1390","1347":"1347","1345":"1345","1442":"1442","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1429":"1429","1390":"1390","Innermaekie, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Moidart, Inverness-shire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1350–1429":"1350–1429","1360–Female":"1360–Kuollut","1375–1442":"1375–1442","1345–1386":"1345–1386","1347–1390":"1347–1390","1347":"1347","1345":"1345","1442":"1442","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1429":"1429","1390":"1390","Innermaekie, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Moidart, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Moidart, Inverness-shire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1350–1429":"1350–1429","1360–Female":"1360–Décédée","1375–1442":"1375–1442","1345–1386